- t "We are Kansas City's Ruby community."

#promo

  .screenshot
    - if @podcast && @podcast.screenshot
      = link_to(image_tag(@podcast.screenshot.url, :size => "345x266", :alt => "Episode #{@podcast.id}"), podcasts_path)

  %h2
    Latest from the
    = "#{link_to "KC Ruby Podcast", podcasts_path}:"
        
  #name
    - if @podcast
      = link_to "Episode 0#{@podcast.id}: #{@podcast.name}", podcasts_path
    

#primary

  %h2 Meetings

  %p
    We meet the second Tuesday of each month at Centriq Training, on State Line Drive.

  %h2 Google Group

  %p
    We run a 
    = link_to "mailing list", "http://groups.google.com/group/kcrug/topics?gvc=2"
    for discussion of Ruby-related topics. If you have a question about Ruby (or Ruby on Rails), 
    this group can probably figure it out.

  %p
    = link_to "Sign up", "http://groups.google.com/group/kcrug"
    or 
    = link_to("browse the archives", "http://groups.google.com/group/kcrug/topics?gvc=2") + "."

  %h2 Need a Ruby Developer?

  %p
    Seeking freelance or fulltime developers? Please post a brief summary of your needs to the 
    = link_to("mailing list", "http://groups.google.com/group/kcrug/topics?gvc=2") + "."

  %p#recruiters
    Recruiters: if you post long job listings, you will be banned.
    Please use a short summary with a link to more information. 
    Check the archives to make sure your listing hasn't been posted by another recruiter.

  %h2 Follow us on Twitter

  %p
    You can follow
    = link_to("@kcrug", "http://twitter.com/kcrug")
    on Twitter for meeting reminders and other updates.
  
/ = render :partial => "sponsors"
